Phase two of the country's vaccination drive kicked off this week countrywide but it hasn't been all smooth sailing. Some 700,000 health workers are still waiting to be vaccinated. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Phase two of the country's vaccination drive kicked off this week countrywide but it hasn't been all smooth sailing. Some 700,000 health workers are still waiting to be vaccinated. READ: Report vaccine side-effects: Govt Health Minister Zweli Mkhize promised to vaccinate them all by Friday but admitted the target is going to be missed. Phase two targets those aged 60 and older while continuing Phase 1-B is aimed at healthcare workers.